✅ 1. No partition mismatch
Each loop processes:

ONE date → ONE partition → ONE SWITCH
✅ 2. No data corruption
Validation ensures:
SQL
COUNT(DISTINCT report_date) = 1
✅ 3. Fully dynamic
No hardcoding:
Dates
Partition numbers
Table data
⚠️ Mandatory Preconditions (don’t skip)
1. Stage table must match structure EXACTLY
SQL
SELECT TOP 0 * INTO dbo.cff_report_stage FROM dbo.cff_report_partitioned;
2. Stage table must have CHECK constraint
Example:
SQL
ALTER TABLE dbo.cff_report_stage
ADD CONSTRAINT chk_stage_partition
CHECK (report_date >= '2026-01-01' AND report_date < '2027-01-01');
👉 Without CHECK → SWITCH fails
3. Indexes must match exactly
Clustered index:
SQL
CREATE CLUSTERED INDEX idx_stage
ON dbo.cff_report_stage(report_date);